125
00:05:11,690 --> 00:05:13,840
- I work for teaching company.

126
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,670
- [Will] What is your job title?

127
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:17,150
- CEO.

128
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,750
- [Will] Do you like your job?

129
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:20,350
- I love my job.

130
00:05:20,350 --> 00:05:23,510
- [Will] What is the most
important part of your job?

131
00:05:23,510 --> 00:05:26,400
- I love teaching my wonderful students.

132
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,810
- [Will] How many days a week do you work?

133
00:05:28,810 --> 00:05:30,100
- Five to seven.

134
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,460
- [Will] Do you have a boss?

135
00:05:31,460 --> 00:05:33,620
- I am my boss, but I
work with my husband.

136
00:05:33,620 --> 00:05:35,420
Sometimes, he bosses me around.

137
00:05:35,420 --> 00:05:37,650
- [Will] What was your first job?

138
00:05:37,650 --> 00:05:40,180
- I was a waitress at the local pub.

139
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:43,280
- [Will] What job would
you never, ever do?

140
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,820
- I don't think I'd like to be a chef.

141
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:46,220
It's too much pressure.

142
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:47,610
- [Will] Would you like a new job?

143
00:05:47,610 --> 00:05:49,580
- No, I'm really happy with this one.

144
00:05:49,580 --> 00:05:52,490
- [Will] Would you recommend
your line of work to others?

145
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:53,940
- If you enjoy teaching,

146
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:56,520
then I think it's a fabulous career path.

147
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,670
- [Will] What did you do this weekend?

148
00:05:58,670 --> 00:06:00,790
- This weekend, we did
a little bit of work

149
00:06:00,790 --> 00:06:03,070
in the morning, and then we relaxed.

150
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:05,210
- [Will] What will you do after work?

151
00:06:05,210 --> 00:06:06,800
- Well, it's quite late right now.

152
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,960
I think we'll eat dinner and go to bed.

153
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,530
- [Will] How was traffic today?

154
00:06:10,530 --> 00:06:11,630
- I didn't drive today.

155
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,800
I work from home.

156
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,850
- [Will] When are you taking time off?

157
00:06:14,850 --> 00:06:18,200
- We are going away
next month on a holiday.

158
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:20,220
- [Will] What will you do on your holiday?

159
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:25,220
- Relax, explore, and
hopefully visit some vineyards.

160
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,970
- [Will] Any plans for the weekend?

161
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:28,760
- This weekend, it's Easter

162
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,490
and we're going to see our families.

163
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:32,070
- [Will] What will you do for lunch?

164
00:06:32,070 --> 00:06:34,800
- Normally, I have a salad for lunch.

165
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:37,180
- [Will] Would you like
to go to lunch with me?

166
00:06:37,180 --> 00:06:38,190
- With you?

167
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:40,070
Every day. (chuckles)

168
00:06:40,070 --> 00:06:41,600
- [Will] Are you working late tonight?

169
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:44,900
- Yes. I'm working unusually late tonight.

170
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:47,190
- [Will] What time did
you clock in this morning?

171
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:50,700
- I started work at
around 8:30 this morning.

172
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,800
- [Will] Did you find a good parking spot?

173
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,799
- I didn't have to park.

174
00:06:53,799 --> 00:06:56,180
(chuckles) I work from home.

175
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:58,280
- [Will] What time do
you get home from work?

176
00:06:58,280 --> 00:07:00,360
- I normally try to finish working

177
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:03,320
at around five to six o'clock.

178
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:04,890
- [Will] How do you get to work?

179
00:07:04,890 --> 00:07:07,560
- I leave my bed, go downstairs,

180
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,400
and sit down at the table.

181
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,610
- [Will] Would you get
public transport to work?

182
00:07:11,610 --> 00:07:12,960
- If I didn't work from home,

183
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:16,060
I would absolutely get
public transport to work.

184
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,350
- [Will] How are your kids?

185
00:07:17,350 --> 00:07:20,570
- I don't have any, yet. (chuckles)

186
00:07:20,570 --> 00:07:22,370
- [Will] Do you ever work overtime?

187
00:07:22,370 --> 00:07:26,360
- Yes. I think it's the nature
of running your own business.

188
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:29,050
- [Will] How many meetings
do you attend in a week?

189
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:32,400
- Probably 7 to 10.

190
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:34,090
- [Will] Did you receive training?

191
00:07:34,090 --> 00:07:36,410
- Yes. I did receive training.

192
00:07:36,410 --> 00:07:39,240
- [Will] Do you think
the company is run well?

193
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:41,170
- I hope so. (chuckles)

194
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:43,210
- [Will] How long have
you been working here?

195
00:07:43,210 --> 00:07:46,890
- I started this business in January 2016.

196
00:07:46,890 --> 00:07:48,710
So is that six years?

197
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:50,600
- [Will] Have you received a promotion?

198
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:55,220
- No. I've always been the CEO. (laughs)

199
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:58,000
- [Will] How often do you get a raise?

200
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:01,600
- I like to pay myself
slightly more each year.

201
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,300
- [Will] How well do you
get on with your boss?

202
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:06,820
- With my business partner, my husband?

203
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,930
Extremely well.

204
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:11,100
- [Will] Do you get on
with your coworkers?

205
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,460
- I have a lovely team.

206
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:16,330
- [Will] What does your
average day look like?

207
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:21,330
- I like to break up my day
with exercise and dog walks.

208
00:08:21,690 --> 00:08:25,150
- [Will] Would you change
anything about your daily routine?

209
00:08:25,150 --> 00:08:27,770
- Yes. I'd like slightly more free time.

210
00:08:27,770 --> 00:08:29,860
- [Will] Do you get to travel for work?

211
00:08:29,860 --> 00:08:32,520
- Before the pandemic,
I travelled quite a lot.

212
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:34,490
It's starting to pick up now.

213
00:08:34,490 --> 00:08:37,799
- [Will] What is the most
challenging part of your job?

214
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:40,499
- Receiving criticism from strangers.

215
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,320
- [Will] Do you have to
work at the weekends?

216
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,500
- Sometimes I do.

217
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,160
In fact, oftentimes I do.

218
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:48,660
- [Will] Does management support you?

219
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:50,483
- My husband is very supportive.

220
00:08:51,390 --> 00:08:53,310
- [Will] How did you find this job?

221
00:08:53,310 --> 00:08:55,230
- I think I was very lucky

222
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:58,160
and a bit lost as a 21-year-old.

223
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:00,120
- [Will] Are you interested in a full-time

224
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,130
or a part-time position?

225
00:09:02,130 --> 00:09:04,440
- I enjoy working in a full-time position,

226
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:06,180
but one day, I might like to move

227
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:08,010
to a part-time position.

228
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:09,760
- [Will] Did you bring your CV?

229
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:10,593
- Do you know what?

230
00:09:10,593 --> 00:09:12,900
